The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Bangalore, April 11: Software major Infosys has sacked nearly 2,100 employees. Some of these employees have been asked to go while some have left on their own, V. Balakrishnan, chief financial officer of Infosys, said. The company had put its employees on a performance improvement course prior to trimming its workforce and those who showed no improvement were asked to leave, while some others quit.                            
	 New Delhi, April 11: Air India has saved over Rs 46 crore in six months till February by implementing several measures to enhance fuel efficiency in its attempts to become a green airline. The national carrier said the total fuel savings projected for the year with revised processes were over 4.56 crore kilolitres.                             
	 New Delhi, April 11: State-run power utilities NTPC, NHPC, PowerGrid and the Damodar Valley Corporation have entered into an agreement to set up a laboratory for testing electrical equipment in the country.                                                                                                                           
